  "prompt": "What is different between Microsoft excel 2007 and Microsoft excle 2013?",
  "response": "Here are some key differences between Microsoft Excel 2007 and Microsoft Excel 2013:\n\nExcel 2007 Features:\n1. Older ribbon interface\n2. Limited data visualization\n3. Basic pivot table functionality\n4. Less cloud integration\n5. 2007 file format (.xlsx)\n6. Limited mobile compatibility\n7. Smaller maximum spreadsheet size\n\nExcel 2013 Features:\n1. Improved ribbon interface\n2. Enhanced data visualization tools\n3. Better pivot table and power pivot capabilities\n4. SkyDrive (OneDrive) cloud integration\n5. Improved file sharing options\n6. Touch-friendly interface\n7. Enhanced 3D mapping features\n8. More advanced charts and graphics\n9. Better performance and faster calculations\n10. Support for larger spreadsheets\n11. Improved data analysis tools\n12. More comprehensive data filtering\n13. Better compatibility with mobile devices\n14. Real-time collaboration features\n15. Enhanced compatibility with web applications\n\nThe primary differences involve improved user interface, better data analysis tools, cloud integration, and enhanced visualization capabilities in Excel 2013 compared to Excel 2007.",
